Boil a full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Set aside.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips, then chop into roughly 1cm pieces.

Trim the @cucumber{1/2} (see ingredients for amount). Use a #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the cucumber, stopping at the seeds.

Trim the @green beans{80%g}, then cut into thirds. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{120%g}, pepper and green beans. Fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once browned, add the garlic to the pan and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Meanwhile, put the cucumber ribbons in a medium #bowl{} with the @rice vinegar{15%ml} and @sugar{1/2%tsp} (see pantry for amount).

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss together. Set aside to pickle.

Add the cooked rice to the beef mixture and stir in the @hoisin sauce{32%g}, @teriyaki sauce{75%g} and @sambal paste{15%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Mix together until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Share the hoisin beef fried rice between your plates.

Serve the pickled cucumber ribbon salad alongside and sprinkle over the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%g} to finish.

Enjoy!

> This delicious Hoisin Beef and Sesame Fried Rice has been expertly designed by our chefs as a lighter option to help with a balanced lifestyle.